      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@Kay I do very much.  An algorithm whose run time increases logarithmically as a function of the number of objects it operates on.  Why did I miscalculate somehow?  Did I misread your code? in it you go through the same string 2 times, the first to count the total the second to append the string and the separator.  Imagine instead of a set of three you had a set of 3 million?  Can you imagine how long the run-time of that solution is?"
