    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You could count the total length of the string first, and pass it to the StringBuilder constructor. And you do not need to convert the Set first.</p>\n\n<pre><code>Set&lt;String&gt; abc = new HashSet&lt;String&gt;();\nabc.add(\"A\");\nabc.add(\"B\");\nabc.add(\"C\");\n\nString separator = \", \";\nint total = abc.size() * separator.length();\nfor (String s : abc) {\n    total += s.length();\n}\n\nStringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(total);\nfor (String s : abc) {\n    sb.append(separator).append(s);\n}\n\nString result = sb.substring(separator.length()); // remove leading separator\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
